\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\b Description\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 The component provides the common functionality and properties for the \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 6>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 TPJWdwState\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 6>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 ,\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 7>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 TPJRegWdwState\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 7>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 and \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 11>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 TPJUserWdwState\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 11>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 components. TPJWdwState\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 ,\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  TPJRegWdwState \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 and TPJUserWdwState \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 simply add the methods \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 and / or events \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 used to store and read window state information and any properties and events relevant to specifying the storage.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 TPJCustomWdwState can be used to derive further window state components that use other forms of storage. To derive a new component the abstract protected methods \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 8>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 ReadWdwState\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 8>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  and \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 9>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 SaveWdwState\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 9>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  must be overidden to read and save window size, position and state information to the desired storage medium.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Instances of \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 this\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  class should not be constructed directly. 
\par }

