{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deftab720\deflang2057{\fonttbl{\f0\fswiss Arial;}{\f1\fmodern Courier New;}{\f2\fswiss \fcharset0 Arial;}}{\colortbl\red0\green0\blue0;\red0\green128\blue0;\red0\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}\pard \plain \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <NS 17>\plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs22\cf3\b TPJCustomWdwState.AutoSaveRestore
\par \plain\f0\fs12\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 18>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 TPJCustomWdwState\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 18>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2           \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 5>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 See also\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 5>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2  \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </NS 17>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Determines whether the window's size, position and state is automatically restored on creation and stored on destruction.
\par 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <KP 1>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2\b property\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  AutoSaveRestore: Boolean;\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </KP 1>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\b Description\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 The AutoSaveRestore property, when set to true, causes the component to automatically restore the owning containing window's size, position and state when the window is created and to save the information when the window is destroyed. 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 The property is normally set at design time. Setting the property at run time has no effect on whether the window's state is restored, since the window will already be created. However, if the property is changed at run time whether the window's display attributes are saved on exit depends on the value of the property (and on whether the \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 2>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Save\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 2>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  method is called\plain\f2\fs18\cf2  from code\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 ).
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 The effect of the property is equivalent to placing a call to \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 3>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Restore\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 3>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  in the form's OnCreate event handler and to a call to \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 4>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Save\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 4>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  in the OnDestroy event handler.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 The default value of this property is False.
\par }

