\par \plain\f0\fs22\cf3\b TPJCustomWdwState.IgnoreState
\par \plain\f0\fs12\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 18>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 TPJCustomWdwState\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 18>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2           \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 3>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 See also\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 3>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2  \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </NS 17>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Determines whether the window's saved state (maximised, normal or minimised) is applied on restoration. \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\b This property is deprecated\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 .
\par 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <KP 1>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2\b property\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  IgnoreState: Boolean;\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </KP 1>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\b Description\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 The IgnoreState property determines the saved state (minimised, maximised or normal) of the window is applied when the window is restored. 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 When the property is true the saved state of the window is ignored and leaves current state unchanged while still setting size and position. When false window restoration also sets the window state to that saved.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 The default value of this property is False.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 The \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 2>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Save\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 2>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  method always records the window state, regardless of the value of IgnoreState.
\par 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\b Note\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 IgnoreState is now deprecated\plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i . \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 This property has the same function as the \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i woIngoreState\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  value in the \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 4>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Options\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 4>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  property. The Options property should be used in preference. IgnoreState is provide\plain\f2\fs18\cf2 d\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  for backwards compatibility.
\par }

