{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deftab720\deflang2057{\fonttbl{\f0\fswiss Arial;}{\f1\fmodern Courier New;}{\f2\fmodern \fcharset0 Courier New;}{\f3\fswiss \fcharset0 Arial;}{\f4\fnil \fcharset2 WingDings;}{\f5\fnil \fcharset0 Arial;}}{\colortbl\red0\green0\blue0;\red0\green128\blue0;\red0\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}\pard \plain \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <NS 17>\plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs22\cf3\b TPJCustomWdwState.Options
\par \plain\f0\fs12\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 18>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 TPJCustomWdwState\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 18>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2           \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 4>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 See also\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 4>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2  \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </NS 17>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Determines how the component interprets the window display data read from storage.
\par 
\par \pard \fi-200 \li200 \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\b type\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  TPJWdwStateOptions = \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\b set of \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 (woIgnoreState, woIgnoreSize\plain\f2\fs18\cf2 , woFitWorkArea\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 );\plain\f1\fs18\cf2\b 
\par \pard \plain\f1\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf1\b \protect <KP 1>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2\b property\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  Options: TPJWdwStateOptions;\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </KP 1>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\b Description\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 The Options property determines various display options used when displaying windows after reading display data from storage. The following values can be included in the Options set.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \pard \fi-1600 \li1600 \tx1600 \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i woIgnoreState\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 \tab Determines the state applied to the window when when restored by the component: minimised, maximised or normal. By default the window is restored to the state read from storage. When this option is specified the stored state is ingored and the window is \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 always \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 displayed in the normal state. Including or excluding this value sets the\plain\f3\fs18\cf2  \plain\f3\fs18\cf2\i deprecated\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 3>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 IgnoreState\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 3>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  property to true or false respectively, and vice versa. This option should be used in preference to IgnoreState, which is deprecated.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i woIgnoreSize\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 \tab Determines the how the size of the stored window is set. By default the window's size is read from storage. When the option is set the stored size is ignored and the window is displayed using its default size: i.e. the size of the window's form as designed.\plain\f3\fs18\cf2  Additionally, setting this option prevents the \plain\f3\fs18\cf2\i woFitWorkArea\plain\f3\fs18\cf2  option from resizing the window.\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i woFitWorkArea\plain\f3\fs18\cf2 \tab When the option is set the restored window appears wholy within the appropriate monitor's desktop work area (i.e. the area of the dektop not occupied by the task bar and any other Windows toolbars). This means that if any part of the restored window would appear outside the work area it is re-positioned to be completely contained in the work area. If the window is too wide or high to fit on the window the action taken depends on the \plain\f3\fs18\cf2\i woIgnoreSize\plain\f3\fs18\cf2  option as follows:
\par \pard \fi-2000 \li2000 \tx1600 \tx2000 \tab \plain\f4\fs18\cf2 \'A7\plain\f5\fs18\cf2 \tab \plain\f5\fs18\cf2\i If woIgnoreSize\plain\f5\fs18\cf2  is not set the window is resized to fit the work area.
\par \tab \plain\f4\fs18\cf2 \'A7\plain\f5\fs18\cf2 \tab if \plain\f5\fs18\cf2\i woIgnoreSize\plain\f5\fs18\cf2  is set then the window size is not changed. The window is aligned so that the top left corner is visible in order to give access to the system menu.
\par \pard \fi-1600 \li1600 \tx1600 \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 \tab When used with MDI child forms this option treats the main MDI form's client area as the work area.
\par \tab When this option is not set the window is not repositioned within the work area.
\par \tab 
\par \pard \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 By default the Options property has value [ ] - the empty set.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 The \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 2>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Save\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 2>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  method always records the window state\plain\f3\fs18\cf2  and size\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 , regardless of the value of \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 the \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i woIgnoreState\plain\f3\fs18\cf2  and \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i woIgnoreSize\plain\f3\fs18\cf2  o\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 ption\plain\f3\fs18\cf2 s. The saved state and/or size is simply ignored when one or both of these option are set.\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par }

