\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 This\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  virtual abstract protected method must be overridden by descendant components to save the Window's state, size and position information to \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 a \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 supported storage type.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 The position of the window is given by the Left and Top parameters, the size by the Width and Height parameters and the State by the State parameter. State is the ordinal value of a member of the TWindowState enumeration: \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i wsMinimized\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 , \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i wsMaximized \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 or \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i wsNormal\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 . The parameter values should be saved in a way that allows them to be identified \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 and associated with the window \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 when reading back in.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 This method is called by the \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 2>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Save\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 2>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  method.
\par }

