\par \plain\f0\fs22\cf1\b \protect <BM 1>\plain\f0\fs22\cf3\b  TPJWdwState\plain\f0\fs22\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs12\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 33>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Heirachy\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 33>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2           \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 34>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Properties\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 34>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2           \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 35>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Methods\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 35>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2           \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 3>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Events\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 3>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2  \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </NS 2>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Non visual component that saves and restores window positions to and from an ini file.
\par 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\b Unit\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 4>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 PJWdwState\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 4>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\b Description\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 This component enables the size, position and state of the form on which it is placed to be saved to and read from an ini file.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 The \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 6>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Save\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 6>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  method saves the window information to a section of an ini file and the \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 7>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Restore\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 7>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  reads information in and sets the owning form window's size, position and state.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 The component's \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 5>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 AutoSaveRestore\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 5>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  property governs whether window \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 sizes, \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 position\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 s\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  and states are automatically restored on opening and saved on closing or whether the user must explicitly call the Save and Restore methods. 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 The \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 8>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 Options\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 8>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  property and the \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 13>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 OnReadWdwState\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 13>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  event can be used to customise how the stored data is interpreted and whether the window's saved state or size should be used or ignored.\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 The ini file to be used is specified using the \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 9>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 IniFileName\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 9>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  property and the name of the section of the ini file to be used is given by the \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 10>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Section\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 10>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  property. Alternatively the \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 11>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 OnGetIniData\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 11>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  event can be handled and used to set the required ini file name and section.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 It is only possible to have one instance of a TPJWdwState component on any one form. Neither can a TPJWdwState component be dropped onto a form that already contains \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 either a \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 12>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 TPJRegWdwState\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 12>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 or a \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 14>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 TPJUserWdwState\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 14>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 component.
\par }

