\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 18>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 TPJWdwState\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 18>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2           \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 4>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 See also\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 4>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2  \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </NS 17>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Determines the name of the ini file used to record window information.
\par 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <KP 1>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2\b property\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  IniFileName: \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\b string\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 ;\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </KP 1>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\b Description\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 This property contains the name of the ini file that will be used to record the window's size, position and state. The file is accessed by both the \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 2>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Restore\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 2>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  and \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 3>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Save\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 3>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  methods.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 The section to use in the ini file is set by the \plain\f2\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 5>\plain\f2\fs18\cf2 Section\plain\f2\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 5>\plain\f2\fs18\cf2  property.\plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 If the property is set to the empty string ('') then the file name used has the same path and file name as the application except that the '.exe' extension is replaced by '.ini'. This is the default value.
\par }

