\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 The class constructor permints an instance of a TPJWdwState component to be placed on a form only if there are no other instances of the component, no instances of \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 3>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 TPJRegWdwState\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 3>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  and no instances of any other component derived from \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 4>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 TPJCustomWdwState\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 4>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  already placed on the form. This restriction is enforced since it makes no sense to have more that one component restoring  the window's size, position and state.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 The constructor also initialises the default property va\plain\f2\fs18\cf2 l\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 ues for the component.
