\par \plain\f0\fs22\cf3\b TPJWdwState.ReadWdwState
\par \plain\f0\fs12\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 18>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 TPJWdwState\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 18>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2           \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 3>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 See also\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 3>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2  \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </NS 17>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Method used to read a window's size, position and state from storage.
\par 
\par \pard \fi-200 \li200 \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\b procedure\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  ReadWdwState(\plain\f1\fs18\cf2\b var\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  Left, Top, Width, Height, State: Integer); \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\b override\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 ;
\par \pard \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\b Description\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 This protected \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 method\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  is overrridden by TPJWdwState to read the Window's state, size and position information from an ini file. Before reading the ini file this method triggers the \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 4>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 OnGetIniData\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 4>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  event to enable the user to change the name of the ini file and the section to use within it where the state data is read.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 The position of the window is returned in the Left and Top parameters, the size in the Width and Height parameters and the State in the State parameter. State is the ordinal value of a member of the TWindowState enumeration: \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i wsMinimized\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 , \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i wsMaximized\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  or \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i wsNormal\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 . The parameters are set to those currently existing for the associated window before calling the method. 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 This method is called by the \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 2>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Restore\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 2>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  method.
\par }

