\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Restores the size, position and state of a window from an ini file.
\par 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <KP 1>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2\b procedure\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  Restore;\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </KP 1>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\b Description\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 This method restores the size and position of the owning form's window according to value saved in a specified section of an ini file. The ini file name is specified by the \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 2>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 IniFileName\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 2>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  property and the section of the file where the data is recorded is given by the \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 3>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Section\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 3>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  property. If the ini file or section do not exist then this method has no effect.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 Various values of the \plain\f2\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 7>\plain\f2\fs18\cf2 Options\plain\f2\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 7>\plain\f2\fs18\cf2  property may cause either the saved size or state to be ignored or for the window to be repositioned (and possibly resized) to fit within the desktop's work area.\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 If the \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 5>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 AutoSaveRestore\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 5>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  property is true \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 Restore\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  is called automatically when the window is created.
\par }

