\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <KP 1>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2\b procedure\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  Save;\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </KP 1>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\b Description\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 This method saves the state, size and position of the owning form's window in an ini file. The ini file name is specified by the \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 2>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 IniFileName\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 2>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  property and the section of the file where the data is stored is given by the \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 3>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Section\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 3>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  property.\plain\f2\fs18\cf2  If the ini file or section do not exist they are created. If it is not possible to create the file or section then the information is not saved.
\par \plain\f2\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 For MDI child forms the window's top and left coordinates are relative to the MDI main form's client area. For other, top level, windows the coordinates are relative to the screen.\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 If the \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 4>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 AutoSaveRestore\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 4>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  property is true then this method is called automatically when the window is destroyed.
\par }

