{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deftab720\deflang2057{\fonttbl{\f0\fswiss Arial;}{\f1\fswiss \fcharset0 Arial;}}{\colortbl\red0\green0\blue0;\red0\green128\blue0;\red0\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}\pard \plain \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <NS 2>\plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs22\cf1\b \protect <BM 1>\plain\f0\fs22\cf3\b  TPJRegWdwState\plain\f0\fs22\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs12\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 33>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Heirachy\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 33>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2           \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 34>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Properties\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 34>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2           \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 35>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Methods\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 35>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2           \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 3>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Events\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 3>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2  \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </NS 2>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Non visual component that saves and restores window positions to and from the registry.
\par 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\b Unit\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 4>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 PJWdwState\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 4>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\b Description\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 This component enables the size, position and state of the form on which it is placed to be saved to and read from the registry.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 The \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 6>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Save\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 6>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  method saves the window information to the registry and the \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 7>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Restore\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 7>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  reads information in and sets the owning form window's size, position and state.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 The component's \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 5>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 AutoSaveRestore\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 5>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  property governs whether window \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 sizes, \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 positions and states are automatically restored on opening and saved on closing or whether the user must explicitly call the Save and Restore methods. 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 The \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 13>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 Options\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 13>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  property and the \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 14>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 OnReadWdwState\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 14>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  event can be used to customise how the stored data is interpreted and whether the window's saved state or size should be used or ignored.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 Application defined data can be read from and written to the registry by handling the \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 15>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 OnGettingRegData\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 15>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  and \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 16>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 OnPuttingRegData\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 16>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  events that are triggered when the component reads and writes its data.\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 The root and sub key to be used in the registry \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 are\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  specified using the \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 9>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Rootkey\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 9>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  and \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 10>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Subkey\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 10>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  properties\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  respectively\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 . Alternatively the \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 11>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 OnGetRegData\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 11>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  event can be handled and used to set the root key and sub key to use.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 It is only possible to have one instance of a TPJRegWdwState component on any one form. Neither can a TPJRegWdwState component be dropped onto a form that already contains \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 either a \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 12>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 TPJWdwState\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 12>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 or a \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 8>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 TPJUserWdwState\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 8>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 component.
\par }

