\par \plain\f0\fs22\cf3\b TPJRegWdwState.RootKey
\par \plain\f0\fs12\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 18>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 TPJRegWdwState\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 18>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2           \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 4>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 See also\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 4>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2  \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </NS 17>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Determines the registry root key under which the window's size, position and state information is stored.
\par 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <KP 1>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2\b property\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  RootKey: HKEY;\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </KP 1>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\b Description\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 This property allows the user to specify under which registry root key the window size, position and state information is recorded. The information is saved in a subkey of this root key. The sub key is determined by the \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 3>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 SubKey\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 3>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  property. The user is responsible for setting the property to a valid HKEY value. Valid values are:
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \pard \li400 \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <KP 2>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT     = $80000000;
\par HKEY_CURRENT_USER     = $80000001;
\par HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE    = $80000002;
\par HKEY_USERS            = $80000003;
\par HKEY_PERFORMANCE_DATA = $80000004;
\par HKEY_CURRENT_CONFIG   = $80000005;
\par HKEY_DYN_DATA         = $80000006;\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </KP 2>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \pard \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 These values are defined in the Windows unit.\plain\f2\fs18\cf2  Note that an optional custom property editor is provided with the components that can display a list of valid HKEY values for this property.\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 The property defaults to HKEY_CURRENT_USER.
\par }

