\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\b Description\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 This method restores the size and position of the owning form's window according to value saved in a specified part of the Windows registry. The root and sub keys of the registry where the information is stored are specfied by the \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 2>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 RootKey\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 2>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  and \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 3>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 SubKey\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 3>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  properties. If the key does not exist in the registry then this method has no effect.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 Various values of the \plain\f2\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 4>\plain\f2\fs18\cf2 Options\plain\f2\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 4>\plain\f2\fs18\cf2  property may cause either the saved size or state to be ignored or for the window to be repositioned (and possibly resized) to fit within the desktop's work area.\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 If the \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 5>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 AutoSaveRestore\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 5>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  property is true \plain\f2\fs18\cf2 Restore\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  is called automatically when the window is created.
\par }

