\par 
\par \pard \fi-200 \li200 \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 TPJWdwStateGetRegData = \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\b procedure\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 (\plain\f1\fs18\cf2\b var \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 RootKey: HKEY;\plain\f2\fs18\cf2  \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\b var\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  SubKey: \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\b string\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 )\plain\f1\fs18\cf2\b  of object;
\par \pard \plain\f1\fs8\cf2\b 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf1\b \protect <KP 1>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2\b property\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  OnGetRegData: TPJWdwStateGetRegData;\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </KP 1>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\b Description\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 This event is triggered just before the registry is read when restoring and saving a window. The \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 current values of the \plain\f3\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 5>\plain\f3\fs18\cf2 RootKey\plain\f3\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 5>\plain\f3\fs18\cf2  and \plain\f3\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 6>\plain\f3\fs18\cf2 SubKey\plain\f3\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 6>\plain\f3\fs18\cf2  properties \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 are passed as var parameters to the event handler, allowing the user to change the values, and hence the location within the registry where the window data is recorded.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 The purpose of the event is to enable the \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 2>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 AutoSaveRestore\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 2>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  property to be used without setting the RootKey and SubKey properties at design time\plain\f3\fs18\cf2   - i.e. handling the event allows either or both of the default RootKey and SubKey values to be overridden.\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par }

