\par \plain\f0\fs22\cf1\b \protect <BM 1>\plain\f0\fs22\cf3\b  TPJ\plain\f1\fs22\cf3\b User\plain\f0\fs22\cf3\b WdwState\plain\f0\fs22\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs12\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 33>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Heirachy\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 33>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2           \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 34>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Properties\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 34>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2           \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 35>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Methods\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 35>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2           \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 3>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Events\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 3>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2  \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </NS 2>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Non visual component that saves and restores window positions to \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 user-provided persistent storage\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 .
\par 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\b Unit\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 4>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 PJWdwState\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 4>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\b Description\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 This component enables the size, position and state of the form on which it is placed to be saved to and read \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 to any persistent storage\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 .\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  The user is responsible for loading and saving the data. This is done by handling the \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 13>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 OnReadData\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 13>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  and \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 14>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 OnSaveData\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 14>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  events. The component is provided in case the user wishes to save to storage other than the registry (use \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 10>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 TPJRegWdwState\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 10>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 ) or ini file (use \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 11>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 TPJWdwState\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 11>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 ).\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 The \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 6>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Save\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 6>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  method saves the window information \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 7>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Restore\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 7>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  reads information in and sets the owning form window's size, position and state.
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 The component's \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 5>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 AutoSaveRestore\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 5>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  property governs whether window \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 sizes, \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 position\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 s\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  and states are automatically restored on opening and saved on closing or whether the user must explicitly call the Save and Restore methods. 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 The \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 8>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 Options\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 8>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  property can be used to customise how the stored data is interpreted and whether the window's saved state or size should be used or ignored.\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 It is only possible to have one instance of a TPJ\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 User\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 WdwState component on any one form. Neither can a TPJ\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 User\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 WdwState component be dropped onto a form that already contains \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 either a \plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 9>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 TPJWdwState\plain\f1\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 9>\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  or a \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 12>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 TPJRegWdwState\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 12>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  component.
\par }

