\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 18>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 TPJUserWdwState\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 18>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2           \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 3>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 See also\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 3>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2  \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </NS 17>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Method used to read a window's size, position and state from storage.
\par 
\par \pard \fi-200 \li200 \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\b procedure\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  ReadWdwState(\plain\f1\fs18\cf2\b var\plain\f1\fs18\cf2  Left, Top, Width, Height,\plain\f2\fs18\cf2  \plain\f1\fs18\cf2 State: Integer); \plain\f1\fs18\cf2\b override\plain\f1\fs18\cf2 ;
\par \pard \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\b Description\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 This protected \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 method\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  is overrridden by TPJUserWdwState\plain\f3\fs18\cf2  \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 to \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 trigger the \plain\f3\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 1>\plain\f3\fs18\cf2 OnReadData\plain\f3\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 1>\plain\f3\fs18\cf2  event that the user must handle to read the \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Window's state, size and position information from \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 persistent storage\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 .
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 The position of the window is returned in the Left and Top parameters, the size in the Width and Height parameters and the State in the State parameter. State is the ordinal value of a member of the TWindowState enumeration: \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i wsMinimized\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 , \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i wsMaximized \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 or \plain\f0\fs18\cf2\i wsNormal\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 . The parameters are set to those currently existing for the associated window before calling the method. 
\par \plain\f0\fs8\cf2 
\par \plain\f0\fs18\cf2 This method is called by the \plain\f3\fs18\cf2 inherited \plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect <HS 2>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2 Restore\plain\f0\fs18\cf1 \protect </HS 2>\plain\f0\fs18\cf2  method.
\par }

